definitions.definition: A coin formerly used in the United Kingdom , Ireland , Malta , Australia , New Zealand and many other Commonwealth countries worth twelve old pence , or one twentieth of a pound sterling .
The currency of Kenya , Somalia , Tanzania and Uganda .
A currency in the United States , differing in value between states.
The Spanish real , formerly having the value of one eighth of a dollar.
